{"id":"428835640537739_491676120920357","type":"photo","created_time":"2013-06-23T06:44:45+0000","message":"Dhaka hit by gas shortage\r\n\r\n\r\nA midnight pipeline leak in the Bibiyana gas-field led to disruption for seven hours in supply to Dhaka.\r\n\r\nComplaints of shortages erupted soon after on Sunday morning.\r\n\r\nA pipe connecting the Chevron gasfield with the national grid had developed leaks around midnight, according to officials.\r\n\r\nIt took the authorities the entire night to fix it.\r\n\r\nMashiur Rahman, operations director of the gas distribution company, Titas, told bdnews24.com that they had detected the leak late last night. \u201cThe plant was shut down and repairs started immediately.\u201d\r\n\r\nUntil the pipelink leak was repaired and the plant went operational at 7am, supply had remained stopped. \u201cBut we tried to prioritise supply for the power plants with the gas that remained in the pipeline.\u201d\r\n\r\nThe Titas official said a number power plants were dependent on its gas supply, so it was incumbent to prioritise their supply. \u201cI hope there won\u2019t be any serious problems.\u201d\r\n\r\nThe officials hoped normal supply would resume by Sunday afternoon.\r\n\r\nOperated by the US-based Chevron, Bibiyana has 2 TCF (trillion cubic feet) of natural gas and produces around 800 MMCFD (million cubic feet per day) most of which goes to meet Dhaka\u2019s daily demand of 1500 MMCF.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, residents from Dhanmondi, Mohammadpur, Khilgaon, Baily Road, Motijheel, Badda, Mohakhali, Kazipara and other areas called bdnews24.com office to complain about the gas shortage in the morning.\r\n\r\nRakib-ul Alam, a resident of Mohammadpur Housing Limited, told bdnews24.com he was out of gas since early morning. \u201cMy office is in Mohakhali, I heard there isn\u2019t any gas there either.\u201d\r\n\r\nTwo of his relatives living in Kazipara and Badda were facing the same crisis.\r\n\r\nKhilgaon resident Fayimuddin Fahim said there was no gas in his locality and at many other places. \u201cI heard there is no gas in Motijheel, Moghbazar, Baily Road as well.\u201d","picture":"https:\/\/fbcdn-photos-c-a.akamaihd.net\/hphotos-ak-ash2\/1043874_491676110920358_413122760_s.jpg"}